13/08/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A joint drill of Romanian and US pilots is under way at the Mihail Kogalniceanu Airport in Constanta, a Romanian Army spokesman said Friday (11 August).
The drill, dubbed "Viper Lance 06", is being held through 25 August and includes 30 troops, 14 F16 fighter planes and 8 MiG Lancer ones.
The aim is to improve interoperability of the two countries' air forces.
(Rompres - 11/08/06)
